# Rasm C# Testing

Read `.claude/skills/cs-testing/SKILL.md`, `tests/csharp/AGENTS.md`, and nearest test `AGENTS.md`. File-specific rules own `*.spec.cs`, `_testkit`, and `*.verify.csx`.

## Rail split

| Rail | Owns |
| --- | --- |
| `rasm-csharp-specs.mdc` | Pure-managed xUnit/CsCheck behavior and law-matrix specs |
| `rasm-testkit.mdc` | Shared generators, oracles, adapters, and scenario capsules |
| `rasm-bridge-scenarios.mdc` | Native Rhino/GH2 runtime paths |
| Architecture tests | Assembly dependency direction only |
| Benchmarks and fuzz | Separate executables, not xUnit |

## Shared Constraints

- Keep static, unit, runtime, benchmark, and fuzz rails independent.
- Keep architecture tests focused on dependency direction, not behavioral assertions.
- Keep benchmarks and fuzz harnesses outside normal xUnit execution.
- Never mirror current implementation output as an oracle.

## Validation ladder

Run `uv run python -m tools.quality test run` for managed specs. Use `uv run python -m tools.quality test run --target <csproj>` for non-default projects. Run `uv run python -m tools.quality bridge verify <scenario-or-glob>` only for bridge-owned runtime behavior.
